author: COMSOL
description: This example illustrates the technique of approximating a thin layer with a surface in diffusion-type problems, which leads to considerable savings in memory usage. In this example the effect of a thin layer with relatively low conductivity on the potential distribution in a structure is studied. The results show that the thin-layer approximation can be valid even for a layer as thick as 10Â percent of the total height of the structure.
